subSubSection.paragraph:
Description.
Male (
holotype
): Fastigium of vertex 1.3 times wider than width of eye. Antennal scapus 2.5 times narrower than fastigium of vertex; 2 times narrower than width of eye; 1.4 times narrower than frontal groove. Pronotum (
Figs. 253–256
) slightly convex in prozona; metazona flattened with relatively wide and blunt median carina; shoulder incision distinct as a concavity; anterior margin almost straight, posterior margin broadly rounded. Tegmina (
Figs. 253–256
) 1.2 times shorter than pronotum, reaching to end of 3rd abdominal tergite, in 
paratypes
from the end of 2nd to end of 3rd tergites; in dorso-lateral view almost triangular, strongly narrowed and apex narrowly rounded. Femora (
Figs. 253
, 
324
) unarmed. Thoracic auditory spiracle long and narrow, in some males more elliptical. Last abdominal tergite (
Figs. 257
, 
326
) with relatively long, narrow and sharp posterior lobes and with deep median incision. Subgenital plate (
Fig. 258
) longer than wide, with a narrow triangular posterior incision, in some males slightly wider; styli long and slender, 1.9 times longer than the depth of posterior incision. Last 3 abdominal tergites with hairy dorsal surface. Cercus (
Figs. 257
, 
327
) slender, long and narrow, with inner tooth in distal part; apical part long and narrow triangular, very slightly recurved. Titillators (
Fig. 328
) slender; apical arms long, thin and slightly curved; basal arms strongly upcurved and widened; toothed middle part slightly convex.
